Consts.useLimit: NB Some features are known to have not been converted in the CAD to GIS conversion. This can happen where the geometry has been created for drawing production. The data is also known to contain duplicates within the same dataset from the same contractor and delivery. Due to the non-delivery of positive negative datasets, where a contractor moved data from one dataset/level to another between revisions (and did not provide an empty dataset to indicate the removal of all features from a dataset/level in the subsequent delivery/revision), there may be some features that appear to be duplicates from the same contractor but from different deliveries, but all being marked as 'Current'. In this latter case select the latest delivery. Geometry QC results: This feature class contains overlapping features.
